concept_explanation.orchestration:
**Orchestration Saga (central coordinator):**

```java
@Service
public class CheckoutSagaOrchestrator {
    public void execute(CheckoutRequest request) {
        SagaState state = new SagaState(request.orderId());
        try {
            inventoryService.reserve(request);  // Step 1
            state.mark(INVENTORY_RESERVED);

            orderService.create(request);       // Step 2
            state.mark(ORDER_CREATED);

            paymentService.charge(request);     // Step 3
            state.mark(PAYMENT_CHARGED);

            notificationService.send(request);  // Step 4
            state.mark(NOTIFICATION_SENT);

        } catch (Exception e) {
            compensate(state, request);  // Run compensations in reverse!
        }
    }

    private void compensate(SagaState state, CheckoutRequest req) {
        // Compensate in REVERSE order:
        if (state.is(PAYMENT_CHARGED))
            paymentService.refund(req.paymentId());    // undo step 3
        if (state.is(ORDER_CREATED))
            orderService.cancel(req.orderId());        // undo step 2
        if (state.is(INVENTORY_RESERVED))
            inventoryService.release(req.itemId());    // undo step 1
    }
}
```

worked_example.final_code:
// Saga steps: forward (reserve, create, charge, notify)
// Compensation: reverse (refund, cancel, release)
// Idempotent: each compensation safe to call multiple times

